# Fuzzywuzzy and Polyfuzz
# Fuzzywuzzy is a handy library for character matching. It can rapidly implement operations like string matching and token matching. 
# It can also readily match entries from several databases.
# Polyfuzz uses transformers, Glove, FastText, and Embeddings to do an efficient match.

pip install fuzzywuzzy
pip install polyfuzz
from polyfuzz.models import TFIDF
from polyfuzz import PolyFuzz
tfidf = TFIDF(n_gram_range=(3, 3))
model = PolyFuzz(tfidf)
model.match(from_list, to_list)

------------------------------------------------------------

# Pyflux designed to deal with time series challenges. 
The module contains several good current time series models, including the Arima, GARCH, and VaR models. 
Finally, flux offers an effective way for time series modelling.

pip install pyflux

